    "Bacher and Madsen (2011) analyzed the model selections and found that the 3R3C model is the minimal best fit model for a 120 m 2 building located in Denmark.",
    "However, it is inconclusive if all buildings of similar size and use can be modeled with 3R3C with the same accuracy.",
    "Lin et al. (2021) build a building model based on information available to minimize the number of uncertain parameters by combining physics-based equations with a neural network.",
    "Other researchers (Daw et al., 2017; Robinson et al., 2022) explored physics-based ML for modeling lake temperature and other dynamical systems.",
    "However, there are limited studies in physics-based ML for building modeling."
